description: Maharashtra Chief Minister and Shiv Sena supremo Uddhav Thackeray targeted BJP at a rally in Mumbai. He criticised BJP over different issues like Killings in Kashmir, providing security cover to leaders, inflation and terrorism. He also took a jibe at BJP over Hanuman Chalisa recitation, Babri Masjid demolition and Hindutva politics. BJP has been attacking Maha Vikas Aghadi (MVA) government led by Uddhav Thackeray. Recently BJP and MNS tried to corner Thackeray government on the use of loudspeakers at religious places. Uddhav Thackeray took on BJP and MNS and gave answers to their questions and criticism. Video by Ramesh Sable
